5) ROLE-BASED ACCESS (components & best practices)
   - Components:
     * User   = individual (stored in User table)
     * Group  = collection of users (team, similar responsibility)
     * Role   = collection of permissions
   - Best practice: assign roles to GROUPS (not to individual users).
     * Easier maintenance: adding/removing users from group changes permissions.
   - Base (out-of-the-box) roles: admin, itil(provide read and write access to itsm applications like incident change), approver_user, catalog_admin, etc.
   - Self-service users: can log in with no roles; limited actions (raise incident, view catalog).
   - Impersonate: admins can impersonate other users to view their UI/permissions.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6) UI (Native) — Key elements & navigation
   - Main screen divided into:
     * Banner Frame (top): logo, user menu, global search, chat, help, settings.
     * Application Navigator (left): All / Favorites / History + filter navigator.
     * Content Frame (center): lists, forms, pages.
     * Edge (available in UI15 only).
   - UI versions: UI16 (default) and UI15 (user-switchable via Settings).

   - Banner Frame details:
     * User menu: profile, impersonate user, elevate roles, logout.
     * Global search: searches across tables; results depend on user's access.
     * Settings: theme, accessibility, list/form personalization, notifications.

   - Application Navigator:
     * All: apps/modules available to user.
     * Favorites: starred items.
     * History: recently visited (configurable timeframe).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7) BRANDING (UI16 config / welcome page)
   - Change via: "UI16 Configuration" (System Properties -> Basic Configuration UI16).
   - Next Experience → Theme and Brand Center (newer configuration model).
   - Can update: instance name, banner image, color theme, date/time format.
   - Welcome page content configurable (short description, links, login messages).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8) LISTS & FILTERS (concepts + operations)
   - List = records from a table (e.g., incident list).
   LIST ELEMENTS
• Title bar, columns, filters, breadcrumbs.
• List menu operations:
  - Create Favorite
  - View (different views)
  - Group By
  - Show (rows per page)
  - Refresh

• Context menu options:
  - Sort
  - Bar / Pie chart
  - Export (CSV, Excel, PDF, JSON, XML)
  - Import
  - Update Selected / Update All

FILTERS
• Built using conditions (field / operator / value).
• “Run” applies filter.
• Breadcrumbs show active filters.
• Save filters with visibility settings (Me / Group / Everyone).

VIEWS
• Different column layouts for different use cases (Default, Mobile, Major Incident).

SEARCH
• Inline search (per-column)
• Global list search (fields included depend on view)
• Search converts into filter conditions

TEMPLATES
• Predefined field values for quickly creating records.
• Scheduled templates can auto-create records on a schedule.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9) FORMS (concepts & config)
   - Form = single record display from a table.
   FORM ELEMENTS
• Form title, UI actions, form menu
• Sections (grouped fields)
• Related Lists (bottom)

SAVE VS SUBMIT
• Save → Save data, stay on form
• Submit → Save and close

FIELD TYPES
• Mandatory fields (red asterisk)
• Read-only fields
• Reference fields (link to another table)
• Choice fields (drop-down)
• Calculated/derived fields (e.g., Priority from Impact + Urgency)

ACTIVITY STREAM
• Work notes & comments tracked as timeline.

FORM CONFIGURATION
1. **Form Layout** — add fields, rearrange, create simple fields.
2. **Form Design** — drag-and-drop designer; create fields; set mandatory/read-only.
3. **Related Lists** — configure related lists shown at bottom.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10) INCIDENT MANAGEMENT (list/form examples)
    • OOB modules include:
  - Create New
  - Assigned to Me
  - All Open
  - All Incidents

• Priority = function(Impact, Urgency) (business rules)
• Templates used for common incident patterns.
• Copy Incident button creates a new record from an existing one.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11) FORM & LIST CONFIGURATION (admin/dev options)
    - Configure accessible via right-click title bar -> Configure -> {Form Layout, Form Design, Related List}.
    - List Configure -> List Layout, List Controls, List Calculation.
    - Form Design: drag field types to create custom fields; name fields; set mandatory/read-only.
    - List Layout: add/remove columns, create fields, set default view.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
12) RELEASE MODEL (Important for admin exam)
-----------------------------------
• ServiceNow now releases **two major versions per year**.
• UI behavior may shift in each release.
• Admins MUST check release notes:
  - UI features (Next Experience updates)
  - Deprecated features (UI15, some legacy components)
  - Updated security/authentication options
  - Workspace improvements
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
13) MISCELLANEOUS
    - Impersonation: used to verify end-user views.
    - Personal Developer Instance: demo instance provided by ServiceNow for practice.
    - Edge element: visible only in UI15.
    - Max rows per page on list: 100.
    - History keeps recent items (default ~10 days; configurable).
    - Favorites: create for quick access; can add icon/color.

