14) KNOWLEDGE CHECK (selected Q&A from transcript)
    Q1: Apps visible to user with NO roles?    => Self-service
    Q2: Edge visible in UI15 or UI16?          => UI15
    Q3: Primary way to access platform data?   => Native UI (platform native UI)
    Q4: Should a role be added directly to user? => False (best practice: add to group)
    Q5: What is a role?                        => Collection of permissions
    Q6: Name two baseline system roles.        => admin, itil (examples)
    Q7: Where is user profile located?         => Banner frame
    Q8: Which button saves and closes form?    => Submit
    Q9: Which button copies incident?          => Copy Incident (form menu)
    Q10: Two ways to configure forms?          => Form Layout, Form Design

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
15) EXAM TIPS (quick)
    - Understand differences: Multi-instance vs Multi-tenant.
    - Remember RBAC hierarchy: User -> Group -> Role (assign roles to groups).
    - Know Save vs Submit behavior on forms.
    - Know how to save/share filters & create favorites.
    - Be familiar with Form Layout vs Form Design steps.
    - Practice: impersonation, saving filters, creating templates, bulk update.
    - Know common auth methods (SSO SAML, LDAP, OAuth, MFA).

